📍SYTK Sullungtang (@sytksullungtang)– Koreatown, LA

Looking for real Korean comfort food? 🍲 At SYTK Sullungtang, they do it the traditional way—no shortcuts, no artificial flavors. Just rich, milky broth simmered for 48 hours to bring out deep, authentic flavor.

🔥 Must-tries:
🥩 Sogogi Suyuk ($38.99) – Tender beef slices + hearty ox knee bone, best with chive salad 
🦴 Ox Knee Bone Soup ($15.99) – Featuring gelatin-rich cartilage in a deep, flavorful broth that celebrates the natural richness of ox knee.
🐮 Short Rib Soup ($15.99) – Another Korean classic, done right.

📍2717 W Olympic Blvd #108, Los Angeles, CA 90006

SoCal Disney Fans! Did you know there’s a Authentic Disney storybook escape in the heart of Temecula 🍷🏰✨
My recent visit to Briar Rose Winery felt like walking straight into a fairytale. Tucked into the hills of Temecula wine country, this isn’t just a winery—it’s a whimsical retreat with deep Disney roots and an atmosphere unlike anywhere else I’ve 
The winery was built by Beldon Fields, a former Disney Imagineer, who modeled the property after Snow White’s cottage. From the moment you arrive, you’re greeted by charming, old-world architecture that looks like it was plucked from an animated classic. Cobblestone paths, timber-framed buildings, flowering vines, and little hidden details all contribute to the enchanted vibe. It’s like stepping into Disneyland’s Fantasyland… but with amazing wine in hand. 🏡🍇✨

The name Briar Rose is a subtle nod to Sleeping Beauty—Princess Aurora’s alias in the forest—and that theme of quiet magic runs through every part of the experience. There’s a sense of peace and wonder here, like time slows down the minute you step through the gate. It’s an homage to storytelling, nostalgia, and craftsmanship—not just in the setting, but in every bottle of wine.

Each wine is artisanally made, and the tasting is by reservation only, so it feels incredibly personal and relaxed. No crowds, no noise—just you, the vines, and the spellbinding charm of a place that feels like it belongs in a Disney movie. ✨🍷

Whether you’re a wine lover, a Disney fan, or just someone who appreciates hidden gems with soul, Briar Rose is a must-visit. Fairytale magic does exist—sometimes you just find it in a glass of red on a sunny Temecula afternoon. 🌹🍷✨

Summer weather never kills our hotpot cravings.  We recently stopped by the Costco in Garden Grove where @sabicofood was doing a special BOGO promotion of their hotpot broths and couldn't resist getting all 4 flavors!

These broth kits come in little jars that have all the spices and ingredients you need for flavorful broth bases.  You just need to add whatever meat, veggies and noodles you prefer.

The flavors available are:

Mongolian 
Sichuan 
Shabushabu
Almond Milk

We tried the Mongolian flavor so far and we were really impressed with how rich and flavorful the broth came out.  We added more ingredients throughout the day and the flavor just kept getting better.  We can't wait to try more!

Check out @sabicofood on Instagram to see where they'll be, or go to sabicofood.com to order online - they have pho broth too!
